3)	"What is git cherry-pick?"

Git cherry-pick is a command used to apply a specific commit from one branch onto another branch. It copies the changes introduced by the selected commit and creates a new commit in the current branch, without merging the entire source branch.
                            .................................................................................................
Git cherry-pick is used to apply a specific commit from one branch to another branch without merging the entire branch.

Command:
git cherry-pick <commit-hash>
Example
Suppose you have:

feature branch with commit abc12
You want only that commit in main
git checkout main
git cherry-pick abc123

Git will copy the changes from commit abc123 and create a new commit on main.
