In our project, we primarily follow the Git Flow branching strategy.
Branches used:
•	main/master – Production-ready code. 
•	develop – Integration branch for ongoing development.  (If needed)
•	feature/* – Created for new features or enhancements. 
•	release/* – Used for release preparation and testing. 
•	hotfix/* – Used for urgent production fixes. 
Workflow:
1.	Developers create a feature branch from develop. 
2.	Changes are committed and pushed to the feature branch. 
3.	A Pull Request (PR) is raised for code review. 
4.	After approval, the feature branch is merged into develop. 
5.	Before deployment, a release branch is created for testing. 
6.	Once validated, the release branch is merged into main and tagged. 
7.	Critical production issues are fixed through a hotfix branch and merged back into both main and develop. 
