8)	Difference between revert, rebase, and merge?

Git Merge combines two branches and creates a merge commit while preserving history. 
Git Rebase moves commits from one branch onto another to create a clean linear history by rewriting commit history.
 Git Revert safely undoes a specific commit by creating a new commit that reverses the changes without modifying existing history.

